WEBVTT

1
00:00:57.600 --> 00:00:58.850
Happy birthday. Randall!

2
00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:01.360
I was at the cliff. I missed you.

3
00:02:04.120 --> 00:02:05.200
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

4
00:02:32.650 --> 00:02:34.756
- I'll catch up with you soon.
- Quinn.

5
00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:37.756
- Well. if it isn't staten kirkland.
- In the flesh.

6
00:02:37.780 --> 00:02:40.030
- Better late than never.
- Quinn.

7
00:02:40.990 --> 00:02:41.990
Staten.

8
00:02:44.040 --> 00:02:45.686
- Davis.
- Great party.

9
00:02:45.710 --> 00:02:48.460
What can I say? I'd do
anything for my nephew.

10
00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:53.210
Look at you. New dress.

11
00:02:53.880 --> 00:02:56.340
- No...
- brings out the Amber flecks in your eyes.

12
00:02:59.140 --> 00:03:00.350
Thank you.

13
00:03:01.510 --> 00:03:05.930
I'll leave you to it. I. I got a big
birthday reveal in the works. so...

14
00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:14.030
- "The Amber flecks in your eyes"?
- He was just being nice.

15
00:03:18.360 --> 00:03:21.556
- It's good to see you out off the ranch.
- It's been a while.

16
00:03:21.580 --> 00:03:24.516
That's what the doctor
prescribes after your wife dies.

17
00:03:24.540 --> 00:03:28.790
Two years of heavy sulking. go
all-out shut-in. grow the beard out.

18
00:03:29.380 --> 00:03:30.470
I love it.

19
00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:35.486
Well. I mean. if you like it...

20
00:03:35.510 --> 00:03:38.100
Might as well keep it. right?

21
00:03:39.970 --> 00:03:41.326
Okay.

22
00:03:41.350 --> 00:03:44.020
Hey. hey. hey. hey.
Shots for the birthday boy.

23
00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:47.246
Always looking for trouble.

24
00:03:47.270 --> 00:03:50.416
Baby. I'm not looking
for trouble. I am trouble.

25
00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:51.980
Reid. here he comes.

26
00:03:52.480 --> 00:03:53.730
Hey. uncle staten.

27
00:03:54.230 --> 00:03:55.810
Hey. boys. Lauren.

28
00:03:56.780 --> 00:03:58.070
Could I get a minute?

29
00:03:58.780 --> 00:03:59.796
Yeah.

30
00:03:59.820 --> 00:04:00.820
Thanks.

31
00:04:06.290 --> 00:04:09.102
Where were you this morning?
I waited at the cliff for you.

32
00:04:09.126 --> 00:04:10.500
I never said I was coming.

33
00:04:11.670 --> 00:04:12.856
It's our tradition. Randall.

34
00:04:12.880 --> 00:04:14.510
Randall!

35
00:04:15.800 --> 00:04:17.010
Hold... hold...

36
00:04:21.840 --> 00:04:23.026
Where are we going?

37
00:04:23.050 --> 00:04:24.380
Trust me. trust me.

38
00:04:25.520 --> 00:04:27.036
- No way!
- Yes!

39
00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:28.310
- What?
- Yes!

40
00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:30.480
Uncle Davis!

41
00:04:31.150 --> 00:04:32.150
Yeah.

42
00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:35.506
Come on. dad! I told
him it was your favorite.

43
00:04:35.530 --> 00:04:36.507
This is sick.

44
00:04:36.531 --> 00:04:40.740
Most of you knew my sister. I know
right now she's looking down on us.

45
00:04:41.450 --> 00:04:42.740
And she's...

46
00:04:44.120 --> 00:04:45.370
She's saying. "Davey..."

47
00:04:47.450 --> 00:04:49.080
"You are spoiling that boy."

48
00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:51.080
As I should.

49
00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:55.290
- Happy birthday. Randall.
- My god. Thank you. uncle Davis.

50
00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:57.460
Enjoy.

51
00:05:05.850 --> 00:05:07.020
Let's go.

52
00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:09.600
You're gonna return that car first thing.

53
00:05:10.390 --> 00:05:12.876
People like Davis do not
give gifts without strings.

54
00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:14.586
What've you got against
uncle Davis anyway?

55
00:05:14.610 --> 00:05:16.626
You act like you're the
only one who lost somebody.

56
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:18.916
- Okay. I'm warning you...
- you're an asshole.

57
00:05:18.940 --> 00:05:21.990
- That is enough!
- God. I wish it was you that died.

58
00:05:25.910 --> 00:05:27.620
Randall! Hey! R...

59
00:06:02.200 --> 00:06:03.200
Yeah. hello?

60
00:06:06.410 --> 00:06:07.950
What are you talking about?

61
00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:32.770
Hey. Quinn.

62
00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:42.950
Let's go. biscuit.

63
00:06:58.580 --> 00:07:02.670
Sorry I'm late. Ellie. Tractor
died again. It's a whole thing.

64
00:07:03.210 --> 00:07:07.696
You realize how long it's gonna take me
to sow three acres of lavender by hand?

65
00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.640
Well. I hate to pile on. but
the banjees just canceled.

66
00:07:13.220 --> 00:07:15.501
- But they're playing tonight.
- Not anymore they're not.

67
00:07:18.350 --> 00:07:21.586
How am I supposed to run a dance hall
when the musical acts keep canceling?

68
00:07:21.610 --> 00:07:23.820
Well. I happen to know a musician.

69
00:07:25.570 --> 00:07:26.626
- No.
- Yes.

70
00:07:26.650 --> 00:07:27.966
- No.
- Why not?

71
00:07:27.990 --> 00:07:29.426
We both know the piano I play

72
00:07:29.450 --> 00:07:32.040
isn't the kind people
around here like to dance to.

73
00:07:33.700 --> 00:07:36.136
That and I'm meeting
staten at the game tonight.

74
00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:37.846
And don't give me that look.

75
00:07:37.870 --> 00:07:38.870
What look?

76
00:07:39.630 --> 00:07:40.760
That look.

77
00:07:42.380 --> 00:07:44.606
Okay. I'm not giving any look.

78
00:07:44.630 --> 00:07:46.316
He's my friend. Ellie.

79
00:07:46.340 --> 00:07:48.470
You and amalah were friends.

80
00:07:49.470 --> 00:07:52.576
It's not your job to put her
husband's heart back in one piece.

81
00:07:52.600 --> 00:07:54.390
And even if it were. Quinn.

82
00:07:55.520 --> 00:07:57.520
I'm not so sure you could. I mean.

83
00:07:58.480 --> 00:07:59.770
not after Randall.

84
00:08:12.330 --> 00:08:13.660
Let's go!

85
00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:16.200
Yeah. baby! Let's go!

86
00:08:19.920 --> 00:08:22.010
Woo-hoo! Spartans!

87
00:08:23.170 --> 00:08:24.510
Go. spartans!

88
00:08:26.590 --> 00:08:28.470
That cherry soda for me?

89
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:32.550
Davis. No. it's not.

90
00:08:33.470 --> 00:08:35.746
- I am wounded. Yeah.
- Are you?

91
00:08:35.770 --> 00:08:37.746
It's all right. You can make it up to me.

92
00:08:37.770 --> 00:08:39.730
- Can I?
- Dinner at Maeve's.

93
00:08:42.480 --> 00:08:44.086
Not exactly the reaction I was hoping for.

94
00:08:44.110 --> 00:08:45.166
I'm sorry.

95
00:08:45.190 --> 00:08:47.796
It's just that you've had a
really long time to ask me that.

96
00:08:47.820 --> 00:08:49.256
You've heard of the friend zone?

97
00:08:49.280 --> 00:08:50.870
That's right here.

98
00:08:51.490 --> 00:08:52.926
But way up here

99
00:08:52.950 --> 00:08:56.216
is the brother of the best friend zone.

100
00:08:56.240 --> 00:09:00.290
That one's real hard to shake
off. In fact. most men don't make it.

101
00:09:01.460 --> 00:09:02.817
You seem to think you have.

102
00:09:02.841 --> 00:09:04.960
Well. you know. Haven't I?

103
00:09:06.380 --> 00:09:09.196
- I don't know.
- Think about it. The offer stands.

104
00:09:09.220 --> 00:09:11.260
I'm a real good time.

105
00:09:22.650 --> 00:09:23.650
Hey.

106
00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:24.980
Hey.

107
00:09:27.020 --> 00:09:29.666
- I feel weird.
- Really? Couldn't tell.

108
00:09:29.690 --> 00:09:31.020
Piss off.

109
00:09:32.360 --> 00:09:34.546
- Nachos?
- Thank you.

110
00:09:34.570 --> 00:09:35.780
Cherry soda?

111
00:09:36.910 --> 00:09:37.767
Thank you.

112
00:09:37.791 --> 00:09:39.920
You're welcome.

113
00:09:50.300 --> 00:09:51.720
I

114
00:09:58.350 --> 00:09:59.940
Okay.

115
00:10:02.730 --> 00:10:04.480
Any sign of that ut scout?

116
00:10:05.860 --> 00:10:08.150
No. no one's ever gonna come out here.

117
00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:29.380
Lucas Russell's having a glow-up.

118
00:10:30.380 --> 00:10:32.106
Really? No. I did not notice.

119
00:10:32.130 --> 00:10:33.816
Okay. guys.

120
00:10:33.840 --> 00:10:35.260
- One on one. Ready!
- Break!

121
00:10:38.720 --> 00:10:39.720
Come on.

122
00:10:43.480 --> 00:10:45.070
Yes! Yes!

123
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:47.586
Shit!

124
00:10:47.610 --> 00:10:49.360
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

125
00:10:52.070 --> 00:10:53.360
Ready! Hut!

126
00:11:10.540 --> 00:11:11.437
Hey.

127
00:11:11.461 --> 00:11:13.130
- You okay?
- Yeah.

128
00:11:14.380 --> 00:11:15.380
Yeah.

129
00:11:22.430 --> 00:11:25.616
- Let's get you out of here.
- No. no. no. I'm fine.

130
00:11:25.640 --> 00:11:27.706
I'm good. You stay.

131
00:11:27.730 --> 00:11:31.360
I'm gonna be by tomorrow
to look after that tractor. Okay.

132
00:11:37.280 --> 00:11:38.320
Hut!

133
00:12:00.430 --> 00:12:03.492
This isn't a good idea.
Lucas. We weren't invited.

134
00:12:03.516 --> 00:12:06.576
Yeah. we're never invited.
It's never a good idea.

135
00:12:06.600 --> 00:12:07.890
Come on. Jack.

136
00:12:39.930 --> 00:12:43.576
What about "this is over" do
you not understand. Reid Collins?

137
00:12:43.600 --> 00:12:46.996
Babe. you said you wanted
space and I gave you space.

138
00:12:47.020 --> 00:12:49.746
- But it's gone on long enough. okay?
- I know.

139
00:12:49.770 --> 00:12:53.246
I just think we want different things.

140
00:12:53.270 --> 00:12:54.296
Right?

141
00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:57.177
I want something that's...
More than this town.

142
00:12:57.201 --> 00:12:59.400
More isn't always better. Lauren.

143
00:13:00.490 --> 00:13:03.450
You'll change your mind. You'll
see. You and me are meant to be.

144
00:13:15.420 --> 00:13:17.090
Ooh. Careful.

145
00:13:17.920 --> 00:13:19.170
That stuff will kill you.

146
00:13:19.760 --> 00:13:21.196
Consider my life saved.

147
00:13:21.220 --> 00:13:24.116
- Means you owe me a blood debt.
- A blood debt?

148
00:13:24.140 --> 00:13:25.270
Is that right?

149
00:13:25.850 --> 00:13:27.230
Now you gotta save me back.

150
00:13:36.520 --> 00:13:37.520
Deal's off.

151
00:13:46.120 --> 00:13:49.016
You don't have to tell me this
town is sitting on liquid gold.

152
00:13:49.040 --> 00:13:51.476
I'm the one who pushed
the permits through city hall.

153
00:13:51.500 --> 00:13:53.102
We appreciate that. Mr. Collins.

154
00:13:53.126 --> 00:13:55.556
<i>but in order to run that
pipeline to the aquifer.</i>

155
00:13:55.580 --> 00:13:58.896
<i>you need to get staten
kirkland and cap Fuller on board.</i>

156
00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:01.026
<i>Without them. the deal is off the table.</i>

157
00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:02.906
Don't worry. I'll get it done.

158
00:14:02.930 --> 00:14:05.287
<i>That second mortgage on
your ranch is depending on it.</i>

159
00:14:05.311 --> 00:14:06.470
Yeah.

160
00:14:15.810 --> 00:14:18.860
- What are you doing?
- Same thing we've been doing for months.

161
00:14:20.230 --> 00:14:22.610
Yeah. but what if Reid sees?

162
00:14:23.150 --> 00:14:24.990
I can take care of myself.

163
00:15:59.080 --> 00:16:00.766
Can I help you. son?

164
00:16:00.790 --> 00:16:04.736
Just heading up to the Fuller
ranch. Got some work lined up there.

165
00:16:04.760 --> 00:16:06.526
I'll give you a ride.

166
00:16:06.550 --> 00:16:07.550
Come on.

167
00:16:12.970 --> 00:16:13.970
Howdy.

168
00:16:14.560 --> 00:16:15.536
Yancy grey.

169
00:16:15.560 --> 00:16:16.457
Sheriff brig man.

170
00:16:16.481 --> 00:16:18.480
Welcome to ransom canyon. yancy.

171
00:16:23.690 --> 00:16:25.530
Where'd you say you were from again?

172
00:16:27.190 --> 00:16:28.190
You know.

173
00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:30.756
Here and there. No place special.

174
00:16:30.780 --> 00:16:32.700
I take it you worked a ranch before?

175
00:16:33.330 --> 00:16:35.420
- Yeah.
- Anywhere I'd know?

176
00:16:39.120 --> 00:16:40.646
- It...
- let me guess.

177
00:16:40.670 --> 00:16:42.510
Here and there. No place special.

178
00:16:46.550 --> 00:16:49.180
Relax. just busting your chops.

179
00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:52.770
Knowing cap Fuller. you might
want to head back to here and there.

180
00:16:54.430 --> 00:16:56.520
- Why is that?
- I guess you'll find out.

181
00:17:20.290 --> 00:17:21.290
You're late.

182
00:17:22.080 --> 00:17:24.460
- Sorry about that. Yancy grey.
- Let's go.

183
00:17:31.970 --> 00:17:33.736
Now the stalls need mucking.

184
00:17:33.760 --> 00:17:36.696
the horses need shoeing.
fences need mending.

185
00:17:36.720 --> 00:17:39.456
Days are long. and we
already agreed on pay.

186
00:17:39.480 --> 00:17:43.110
That is... well. I don't
renegotiate. you got it?

187
00:17:44.230 --> 00:17:46.320
- I'm your man. Mr. Fuller.
- Your new digs.

188
00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:52.070
That a problem?

189
00:17:53.610 --> 00:17:54.900
Feels like home already.

190
00:18:32.610 --> 00:18:34.320
Morning to you too. staten.

191
00:18:39.200 --> 00:18:40.530
Come on. biscuit.

192
00:18:49.590 --> 00:18:50.590
Cap?

193
00:18:51.670 --> 00:18:52.750
You in here?

194
00:19:02.180 --> 00:19:03.706
Just who in the hell are you?

195
00:19:03.730 --> 00:19:05.480
Damn!

196
00:19:08.270 --> 00:19:09.546
I think you'll survive.

197
00:19:09.570 --> 00:19:12.360
- Is that your medical opinion?
- Matter of fact. it is.

198
00:19:12.990 --> 00:19:14.240
I used to be a nurse.

199
00:19:16.610 --> 00:19:18.846
Sorry if I... rattled you.

200
00:19:18.870 --> 00:19:19.950
Don't be.

201
00:19:20.870 --> 00:19:23.540
You didn't. You gonna
tell me who you are now?

202
00:19:24.040 --> 00:19:26.210
- Cap's new foreman.
- Right!

203
00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:28.670
- Randy.
- Yancy.

204
00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:32.276
And you are?

205
00:19:32.300 --> 00:19:34.260
Ellie estevez.

206
00:19:35.170 --> 00:19:39.300
Cap and my pops go way
back. so I pop in. keep an eye out.

207
00:19:39.800 --> 00:19:41.220
do some errands for him.

208
00:19:41.720 --> 00:19:45.456
Actually. would you mind
taking this to the house?

209
00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:48.746
Blood pressure meds. I'm
kinda running late for work.

210
00:19:48.770 --> 00:19:50.560
- Hospital?
- Bar.

211
00:19:51.060 --> 00:19:52.980
Well. dance hall.

212
00:19:54.650 --> 00:19:57.240
You should. stop by.

213
00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:00.466
"Welcome to ransom" drinks on me.

214
00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:02.080
I just might do that.

215
00:20:05.580 --> 00:20:08.040
It's nice to meet you. Ellie estevez.

216
00:20:21.600 --> 00:20:23.480
Look at you.

217
00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:51.670
What the hell?

218
00:20:58.590 --> 00:20:59.946
Hey. thanks for the ride.

219
00:20:59.970 --> 00:21:03.406
- Don't forget. rent is due today.
- Yeah. yeah. I got it handled.

220
00:21:03.430 --> 00:21:04.930
Keep focusing on school. all right?

221
00:21:10.390 --> 00:21:12.100
And stay out of trouble. kit.

222
00:21:26.910 --> 00:21:29.410
Way to shoot your shot. bro.

223
00:21:33.460 --> 00:21:35.186
- Guess what?
- What?

224
00:21:35.210 --> 00:21:39.066
Turns out ut's scout
was at the game after all.

225
00:21:39.090 --> 00:21:39.987
Shut up.

226
00:21:40.011 --> 00:21:42.822
She wants us to come to
Austin for their cheer clinic.

227
00:21:42.846 --> 00:21:45.826
- You know what this could mean?
- It could mean a full ride to ut!

228
00:21:45.850 --> 00:21:48.850
- That's right. We did it. bitch.
- We did it. yeah!

229
00:21:56.320 --> 00:21:58.030
Would you like some pie?

230
00:22:00.940 --> 00:22:03.426
- Needs a new belt. doesn't it?
- Yep.

231
00:22:03.450 --> 00:22:06.120
- Did I not say it was the belt?
- You did.

232
00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:07.950
And you were right.

233
00:22:09.910 --> 00:22:12.476
Sorry about last night.
Shouldn't have pushed you to go.

234
00:22:12.500 --> 00:22:16.856
No. you didn't... You
didn't push. It's fine.

235
00:22:16.880 --> 00:22:20.380
I just... I guess I just
wanted... Wanted to what?

236
00:22:22.170 --> 00:22:24.670
What. ease me back
into the world of the living?

237
00:22:25.470 --> 00:22:26.470
Yeah.

238
00:22:26.850 --> 00:22:27.850
I get it.

239
00:22:31.310 --> 00:22:32.600
I can do that.

240
00:22:33.350 --> 00:22:34.350
Already done.

241
00:22:56.460 --> 00:22:58.710
You used to wear your
hair like that in high school.

242
00:23:01.090 --> 00:23:02.090
Yeah.

243
00:23:07.260 --> 00:23:10.446
Okay. well. I'll figure that belt
out and get back to you tomorrow.

244
00:23:10.470 --> 00:23:11.550
All right.

245
00:23:12.970 --> 00:23:15.140
Yeah. okay. I'll see you then.

246
00:23:30.950 --> 00:23:33.160
I'm gonna need a drink for this.

247
00:23:37.330 --> 00:23:38.830
So...

248
00:23:39.540 --> 00:23:41.750
To what do I owe the pleasure. Davis?

249
00:23:42.550 --> 00:23:44.402
You're really gonna make me say it?

250
00:23:44.426 --> 00:23:47.986
Well. I know it's not because you want me
to sell my land to those Austin water boys

251
00:23:48.010 --> 00:23:50.720
so they can build their
damn pipeline. right?

252
00:23:52.260 --> 00:23:53.300
This is my home.

253
00:23:55.060 --> 00:23:56.060
I know.

254
00:23:56.390 --> 00:23:57.930
And it will stay that way.

255
00:23:58.440 --> 00:24:00.376
They'll guarantee a leaseback.

256
00:24:00.400 --> 00:24:01.480
Nothing changes.

257
00:24:02.230 --> 00:24:06.426
Except you. me. and cap will
all be. several million richer.

258
00:24:06.450 --> 00:24:08.256
Yeah. I don't need any more money.

259
00:24:08.280 --> 00:24:09.820
Yeah. I know you don't.

260
00:24:10.370 --> 00:24:14.266
But. you know. you inherited
60.000 acres in a trust fund. so...

261
00:24:14.290 --> 00:24:17.420
Yeah. well. you're not doing
so bad yourself. are you?

262
00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:21.710
Staten...

263
00:24:22.460 --> 00:24:25.420
This would be good
for ransom. for the town.

264
00:24:26.260 --> 00:24:29.276
Look. don't be so provincial. Think
about people apart from yourself for once.

265
00:24:29.300 --> 00:24:30.890
You got no goddamn sense.

266
00:24:33.560 --> 00:24:34.980
The world's drying up.

267
00:24:35.520 --> 00:24:38.536
That aquifer feeds our Wells.
our crops. and our cattle.

268
00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:41.310
and I'm not gonna let them
run it dry. You understand?

269
00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:47.530
Staten. the town has already
granted permission for the pipeline.

270
00:24:49.450 --> 00:24:52.080
It's only a matter of
time until I find a way.

271
00:24:52.570 --> 00:24:55.240
with or without you.

272
00:25:01.290 --> 00:25:02.630
Thanks for the drink.

273
00:25:22.520 --> 00:25:24.126
Hey.

274
00:25:24.150 --> 00:25:26.860
It's okay. It's okay. it's okay. it's okay.

275
00:25:27.530 --> 00:25:29.216
Hey. it's all right.

276
00:25:29.240 --> 00:25:31.280
It's all right.

277
00:25:32.360 --> 00:25:35.910
You gotta be patient. all right?
Breaking a horse takes time.

278
00:25:37.080 --> 00:25:38.330
All right. Come on.

279
00:25:39.040 --> 00:25:40.710
It's okay. It's okay.

280
00:25:47.380 --> 00:25:48.380
Ready. boss?

281
00:27:07.580 --> 00:27:09.080
What you got there. staten?

282
00:27:11.210 --> 00:27:12.250
An answer.

283
00:27:21.390 --> 00:27:22.996
Who the hell's that?

284
00:27:23.020 --> 00:27:26.496
Looks like Austin water & power
surveying for the pipeline again.

285
00:27:26.520 --> 00:27:27.690
God damn it.

286
00:27:28.860 --> 00:27:32.046
All right. you tell them
that this is private property.

287
00:27:32.070 --> 00:27:35.700
If they don't leave. you shoot 'em.
Kidding. Just... just get rid of 'em.

288
00:27:48.330 --> 00:27:49.580
There it is.

289
00:27:50.750 --> 00:27:51.960
There's your proof.

290
00:27:53.210 --> 00:27:54.250
Proof of what exactly?

291
00:27:55.130 --> 00:27:57.590
Proof there was another
car on the road that night.

292
00:27:59.550 --> 00:28:02.140
Dan. I'm... listen. I'm telling you.

293
00:28:03.890 --> 00:28:05.310
Somebody else made him crash.

294
00:28:06.140 --> 00:28:09.166
Look. I know this is hard.
today being a year and all.

295
00:28:09.190 --> 00:28:12.110
But your boy was alone out
there that night. You understand?

296
00:28:13.400 --> 00:28:14.780
You gotta let this theory go.

297
00:28:17.650 --> 00:28:18.650
Staten...

298
00:28:19.570 --> 00:28:22.386
Hey. Have you thought
about taking a break?

299
00:28:22.410 --> 00:28:24.216
Maybe giving yourself a little vacation?

300
00:28:24.240 --> 00:28:27.346
Well. I'm just saying it
might do you some good.

301
00:28:27.370 --> 00:28:29.250
Might... might do me some good?

302
00:28:30.170 --> 00:28:33.880
You know what would do me some
good. Dan. is if you did your goddamn job.

303
00:28:39.880 --> 00:28:42.010
Why do you let him talk
to you like that. sheriff?

304
00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:47.230
Well. because that man has
lost everything he loves. Kai.

305
00:28:48.730 --> 00:28:50.650
And he's looking for a reason.

306
00:28:51.480 --> 00:28:53.020
Even if there isn't one.

307
00:29:26.140 --> 00:29:27.730
Want me to get in there?

308
00:29:28.810 --> 00:29:29.940
Smaller hands.

309
00:29:31.100 --> 00:29:32.350
No. I'll get it.

310
00:29:47.910 --> 00:29:49.370
Hey.

311
00:29:50.790 --> 00:29:51.790
Talk to me.

312
00:29:54.330 --> 00:29:55.370
I'm good.

313
00:30:01.300 --> 00:30:03.300
Would you just let me fix the damn belt?

314
00:30:04.840 --> 00:30:07.260
Yeah. you know what? Have at it. staten.

315
00:30:33.040 --> 00:30:35.266
My mom's a drunk. and
I'm the one who has to stay.

316
00:30:35.290 --> 00:30:38.316
Come on. Your dad wouldn't
make you give up a full ride at ut.

317
00:30:38.340 --> 00:30:39.420
Well. he did.

318
00:30:40.380 --> 00:30:44.340
He doesn't realize being stuck here
is what made my mom the way she is.

319
00:30:47.140 --> 00:30:49.350
I just don't want to end up like her.

320
00:30:50.470 --> 00:30:51.470
I won't.

321
00:30:51.810 --> 00:30:52.850
Hey.

322
00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:56.820
I'm not gonna let that happen.

323
00:31:15.670 --> 00:31:17.960
Not gonna use the power sander?

324
00:31:19.710 --> 00:31:21.460
- You got a power sander?
- Yup.

325
00:31:23.670 --> 00:31:26.906
Might have been. helpful to
let me know before I started.

326
00:31:26.930 --> 00:31:29.600
Well. I'm not one to micromanage.

327
00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:39.086
Don't get up.

328
00:31:39.110 --> 00:31:40.940
I know how hard that
is for you these days.

329
00:31:42.480 --> 00:31:45.546
Couple years ago. I'd have
whooped your ass bad for that.

330
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:48.426
- Think we both know you still could.
- You want a beer?

331
00:31:48.450 --> 00:31:50.910
No. no. I'm set. How you doing. old boy?

332
00:31:51.870 --> 00:31:55.726
You... getting charitable over here?

333
00:31:55.750 --> 00:31:58.016
We'll see how long he lasts.

334
00:31:58.040 --> 00:32:00.040
What's eating at you?

335
00:32:02.340 --> 00:32:04.486
Austin water & power.

336
00:32:04.510 --> 00:32:06.652
They been dripping
honey in your ear too?

337
00:32:06.676 --> 00:32:07.946
They're trying to.

338
00:32:07.970 --> 00:32:11.826
Davis came by. wants
me to sit down with 'em.

339
00:32:11.850 --> 00:32:14.162
I think we need to lock arms on this. cap.

340
00:32:14.186 --> 00:32:17.416
Let me talk to the utilities commission
and have them run some oversight.

341
00:32:17.440 --> 00:32:19.706
The numbers they're
batting around ain't nothing.

342
00:32:19.730 --> 00:32:21.376
Yeah. I know the numbers. all right?

343
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:23.490
But these are our
homes we're talking about.

344
00:32:24.190 --> 00:32:25.900
These ranches are our legacy.

345
00:32:27.360 --> 00:32:28.690
Legacy to who?

346
00:32:29.490 --> 00:32:30.870
Our sons are dead.

347
00:32:51.260 --> 00:32:52.680
What can I get you?

348
00:32:54.140 --> 00:32:55.230
Shiner'd be nice.

349
00:33:10.530 --> 00:33:11.676
Did I miss something here?

350
00:33:11.700 --> 00:33:14.290
I saw that article in your little book.

351
00:33:14.990 --> 00:33:16.266
I care about cap.

352
00:33:16.290 --> 00:33:20.436
You could work at half a
dozen ranches for twice the pay.

353
00:33:20.460 --> 00:33:22.856
It just didn't make any sense. And then I.

354
00:33:22.880 --> 00:33:24.970
and then you thought the worst. I get it.

355
00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:30.710
Look. far as other ranches are concerned.
the last place I was at didn't go so well.

356
00:33:31.220 --> 00:33:33.890
Cap was the only one that
didn't ask for references.

357
00:33:34.390 --> 00:33:35.640
As far as that paper.

358
00:33:36.140 --> 00:33:38.246
I was just trying to see
what his place used to be.

359
00:33:38.270 --> 00:33:39.900
see if I could help bring it back.

360
00:33:41.350 --> 00:33:42.350
And that's it?

361
00:33:43.270 --> 00:33:44.270
That's it.

362
00:33:48.900 --> 00:33:51.240
You so much as cross that old man.

363
00:33:52.530 --> 00:33:54.280
I will see to it you suffer.

364
00:33:58.870 --> 00:34:00.000
Yes. ma'am.

365
00:34:07.880 --> 00:34:08.880
Cheers!

366
00:34:15.890 --> 00:34:17.020
Yo. Lucas.

367
00:34:18.350 --> 00:34:20.310
When are you gonna
come work for my dad. man?

368
00:34:21.230 --> 00:34:24.126
- What?
- I mean. like. your brother's there now.

369
00:34:24.150 --> 00:34:26.570
You know. your old man
was there back in the day.

370
00:34:27.230 --> 00:34:30.860
Just a regular Russell family tradition.

371
00:34:31.440 --> 00:34:32.570
Yeah. I guess so.

372
00:34:35.740 --> 00:34:37.870
Your dad taught me how
to ride when I was a kid.

373
00:34:41.080 --> 00:34:43.420
- I didn't know that.
- He was a hell of a wrangler too.

374
00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:46.000
That he was.

375
00:35:04.060 --> 00:35:05.060
Hey.

376
00:35:05.690 --> 00:35:08.706
- What are y'all doing up here?
- You're just in time.

377
00:35:08.730 --> 00:35:11.270
I was about to clear
something up with Lucas here.

378
00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:15.756
You need to leave my woman alone.

379
00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:17.280
My god.

380
00:35:17.870 --> 00:35:20.636
I'm sorry. I think I'm mistaken.
Do we have a problem here?

381
00:35:20.660 --> 00:35:23.250
You gotta be kidding me with
this toxic male whatever this is.

382
00:35:23.830 --> 00:35:25.750
Really? Lucas. let's go.

383
00:35:26.710 --> 00:35:27.710
Come on.

384
00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:32.396
Cops!

385
00:35:32.420 --> 00:35:33.736
Yo. check it out. check it out!

386
00:35:33.760 --> 00:35:37.810
No. no!

387
00:35:49.310 --> 00:35:52.046
God. Did any of you guys drive?

388
00:35:52.070 --> 00:35:53.586
- No.
- Ben was designated.

389
00:35:53.610 --> 00:35:55.150
I don't have a car.

390
00:35:55.990 --> 00:35:56.990
Great.

391
00:35:58.070 --> 00:35:59.070
Okay. well...

392
00:36:00.030 --> 00:36:02.990
Yeah. we have no service
either. so we're stranded.

393
00:36:06.160 --> 00:36:08.346
- Whoa.
- Hey. how is this my fault?

394
00:36:08.370 --> 00:36:10.000
- Let's go.
- What'd I do?

395
00:36:13.920 --> 00:36:15.550
You were not at that show.

396
00:36:16.260 --> 00:36:18.827
Rampart theater. back
row. I swear to god.

397
00:36:18.851 --> 00:36:20.986
You are full of it.

398
00:36:21.010 --> 00:36:23.550
Okay. listen.

399
00:36:24.810 --> 00:36:26.116
I was at school.

400
00:36:26.140 --> 00:36:29.270
Amalah told me that you
had a showcase concert.

401
00:36:30.440 --> 00:36:33.820
So I went into the city
and I. saw you play.

402
00:36:34.360 --> 00:36:36.650
You were... you were unbelievable.

403
00:36:39.660 --> 00:36:42.846
Okay. in case it hasn't
been abundantly clear.

404
00:36:42.870 --> 00:36:45.460
I've had a thing for you
since... since forever.

405
00:36:46.200 --> 00:36:48.556
Look. I... I was always worried that you...

406
00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:51.186
You know. you wouldn't
see me as anything more

407
00:36:51.210 --> 00:36:55.646
than your best friend's little brother
who was utterly infatuated with you.

408
00:36:55.670 --> 00:37:00.590
And yet you've been utterly
infatuated before. Mr. Collins.

409
00:37:02.180 --> 00:37:03.037
I was at your wedding.

410
00:37:03.061 --> 00:37:04.736
Both of them.

411
00:37:04.760 --> 00:37:07.180
Whatever happened to miss Texas?

412
00:37:09.890 --> 00:37:11.680
- It's complicated.
- Okay.

413
00:37:14.940 --> 00:37:18.150
So... Why didn't you go back?

414
00:37:18.740 --> 00:37:21.410
When amalah got sick and
you came home from New York?

415
00:37:22.450 --> 00:37:23.990
Why didn't you go back?

416
00:37:27.950 --> 00:37:29.280
It's complicated.

417
00:37:34.750 --> 00:37:36.896
Hey. June. I'm here to pick up.

418
00:37:36.920 --> 00:37:38.026
Coming right up.

419
00:37:38.050 --> 00:37:39.130
Thank you.

420
00:37:50.850 --> 00:37:53.286
Tell your buddies at Austin
water & power to stop calling.

421
00:37:53.310 --> 00:37:54.980
because I'm not selling. You understand?

422
00:38:02.200 --> 00:38:03.780
Yeah. sorry about that.

423
00:38:13.750 --> 00:38:14.750
Well...

424
00:38:33.600 --> 00:38:35.520
What the hell is she doing with Davis?

425
00:38:36.730 --> 00:38:38.150
My god.

426
00:38:41.900 --> 00:38:43.256
Please. be quiet!

427
00:38:43.280 --> 00:38:44.926
Hey! Hey!

428
00:38:44.950 --> 00:38:46.870
Hey!

429
00:38:48.410 --> 00:38:50.830
And the Darwin award goes to...

430
00:38:57.210 --> 00:38:59.670
All right. There. Let's
take cover over there.

431
00:39:00.250 --> 00:39:01.436
Ghost house? No way. man.

432
00:39:01.460 --> 00:39:03.340
Fine. Freeze.

433
00:39:20.190 --> 00:39:21.376
Guys

434
00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.320
Reid. I don't have a
good feeling about this.

435
00:39:24.320 --> 00:39:26.070
This floor isn't stable.

436
00:39:28.120 --> 00:39:29.097
Hey. stop.

437
00:39:29.121 --> 00:39:30.926
- It's gonna be fine.
- Don't. man.

438
00:39:30.950 --> 00:39:32.176
- What?
- Reid. stop.

439
00:39:32.200 --> 00:39:33.240
Reid. no!

440
00:39:34.250 --> 00:39:35.460
God.

441
00:39:37.170 --> 00:39:38.920
- Over there!
- My leg!

442
00:39:44.220 --> 00:39:45.350
Lauren. come on.

443
00:39:47.090 --> 00:39:48.090
Lauren?

444
00:39:52.640 --> 00:39:54.156
Look at me. Walk to me.

445
00:39:54.180 --> 00:39:55.600
I can't move. I can't move.

446
00:40:02.480 --> 00:40:04.006
Don't... don't let me fall.

447
00:40:04.030 --> 00:40:05.110
I won't.

448
00:40:08.660 --> 00:40:10.040
I've got you.

449
00:40:11.200 --> 00:40:13.490
I got you. Come on.

450
00:40:15.580 --> 00:40:16.670
Tim?

451
00:40:20.540 --> 00:40:21.540
Tim!

452
00:40:24.210 --> 00:40:25.210
God.

453
00:40:41.020 --> 00:40:42.020
Come on.

454
00:40:44.900 --> 00:40:45.990
You guys stay put.

455
00:40:46.610 --> 00:40:47.940
Sheriff's on his way.

456
00:40:54.740 --> 00:40:57.306
Look. all right. I could
tell the floor was unsafe.

457
00:40:57.330 --> 00:40:59.920
And I tried to get 'em to stop
horsing around over there.

458
00:41:00.500 --> 00:41:02.936
They didn't. And then the floor gave out.

459
00:41:02.960 --> 00:41:03.960
Nuh.

460
00:41:04.550 --> 00:41:07.680
- No. I'm gonna tell him the truth.
- Let's let him play the hero.

461
00:41:08.550 --> 00:41:10.406
But. Lucas. this is just wrong. Like

462
00:41:10.430 --> 00:41:11.640
you know the truth.

463
00:41:12.430 --> 00:41:14.140
That's all that matters to me.

464
00:41:22.150 --> 00:41:23.257
Is that your dad?

465
00:41:23.281 --> 00:41:25.190
Shit!

466
00:41:26.320 --> 00:41:29.216
Dad. listen. I'm fine. okay?
Give me a minute to explain

467
00:41:29.240 --> 00:41:30.330
not right now.

468
00:41:30.910 --> 00:41:34.230
I'm still mentally composing the lecture
I'm gonna be giving you the next 10 years.

469
00:41:37.080 --> 00:41:40.130
- Let's go.
- 3-1. what's your 20?

470
00:41:46.210 --> 00:41:48.420
<i>Sarge. this is 4-9 Charlie.</i>

471
00:41:49.760 --> 00:41:51.816
I'm gonna say this once and only once.

472
00:41:51.840 --> 00:41:53.116
You stay away from that boy.

473
00:41:53.140 --> 00:41:55.747
- That Russell family is trouble.
- But. dad. you don't understand

474
00:41:55.771 --> 00:41:57.090
it's not up for discussion.

475
00:41:57.640 --> 00:41:59.996
Now. I am willing to
reconsider that cheer clinic.

476
00:42:00.020 --> 00:42:02.610
at least for now. but this...

477
00:42:03.480 --> 00:42:04.980
This is my one condition.

478
00:42:30.800 --> 00:42:33.736
- Hey. Don't worry. Your nephew's okay.
- What happened?

479
00:42:33.760 --> 00:42:35.760
He's banged up.

480
00:42:36.430 --> 00:42:39.406
Broken legs and busted
ribs. but he's gonna be fine.

481
00:42:39.430 --> 00:42:40.786
Your sister's in there now.

482
00:42:40.810 --> 00:42:41.890
Thank you.

483
00:42:42.810 --> 00:42:44.310
So. Davis?

484
00:42:49.730 --> 00:42:51.570
Now's not really the best time.

485
00:42:53.070 --> 00:42:54.070
All right.

486
00:42:56.160 --> 00:42:57.750
You're unbelievable. you know that?

487
00:43:01.410 --> 00:43:04.136
You've had a piece of my heart
for as long as I can remember.

488
00:43:04.160 --> 00:43:05.976
- Hold on. What are...
- listen.

489
00:43:06.000 --> 00:43:08.250
I buried it when you and
amalah started dating.

490
00:43:09.550 --> 00:43:12.010
Buried it even more
when you two got married.

491
00:43:13.340 --> 00:43:16.550
I moved halfway across
the country to avoid it.

492
00:43:22.140 --> 00:43:24.930
When she got sick. I
was here for her and you.

493
00:43:26.310 --> 00:43:29.560
And I've been here ever
since. through all of it.

494
00:43:31.230 --> 00:43:32.360
Through the pain.

495
00:43:34.110 --> 00:43:35.110
the grief.

496
00:43:38.030 --> 00:43:39.160
Through Randall.

497
00:43:43.000 --> 00:43:44.710
And I've waited.

498
00:43:45.960 --> 00:43:47.920
I've waited for you to heal...

499
00:43:50.880 --> 00:43:52.050
To choose me.

500
00:43:54.090 --> 00:43:56.470
But you're never gonna do that. are you?

501
00:44:00.720 --> 00:44:01.720
Quinn. I...

502
00:44:09.860 --> 00:44:11.610
Why do you care what I do?

503
00:44:17.610 --> 00:44:18.740
I don't.

504
00:44:43.010 --> 00:44:44.180
Damn it.

505
00:45:35.270 --> 00:45:36.730
All's going to plan with cap.

506
00:45:37.610 --> 00:45:39.530
But you didn't tell me about the girl.

507
00:45:41.950 --> 00:45:42.950
Does it matter?

508
00:45:48.500 --> 00:45:49.960
We're sure about this?

509
00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:55.010
'Cause once you go through
with it. there's no going back.

510
00:45:58.010 --> 00:45:59.430
That's what I'm counting on.
